Russia Allows Pork Imports From Two U.S. Meat Plants, USDA Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-03-28T16:49:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/russia-allows-pork-imports-from-two-u-s-meat-plants-usda-says.html
Russia is allowing imports from two
U.S. hog slaughterhouses and banning shipments from two cold-
storage facilities, the Department of Agriculture said  Russia will allow shipments from Swift Pork Co.’s facility
in Marshalltown, Iowa, and John Morrell’s plant in  Sioux Falls ,
South Dakota, as of March 23, the USDA’s Food Safety and
Inspection Service said in a  report  dated March 24 on its
website.  Russia won’t accept pork shipments from Atlantic Coast
Freezer LLC in Vineland,  New Jersey , and Frozen Assets Cold
Storage in Chicago as of March 24, the agency said. The reason
for the bans wasn’t provided.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
 ecampbell14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick McKiernan at 
 pmckiernan@bloomberg.net  